node.text: When do you like to throw the Neko Rig?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 02, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, beard and text that says 'Karl's FISHING 101: Neko Rig TRUMA'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'WHAT IS IT? Basically, it's a weighted version of a wacky rig. Almost like a ned rig and wacky rig hybrid! A nail weight is inserted into one end of the soft plastic which gives it a unique action, and allows it to stand straight up off the bottom.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'RIGGING TIP Use a tough soft plastic so the nail weight does not fall out of it, and be sure it's in there tight. If not you'll be losing a lot of gear! actua Use an nail weight if possible, but if not just buy small nails at the local hardware store.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'HOW TO FISH IT Neko rigs get hit on the fall a lot, so you'll want to let it sink all the way. Once on the bottom you can hop it, add pauses, and even swim it a little. However, maintaining bottom contact is where it thrives!'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 02, 2021. May be an image of body of water and text that says 'WHERE TO FISH IT Finesse rigs are often limited to water less than 8 feet, but the neko rig allows you to have a wacky rig presentation in deep water. Try it: -If fish are feeding on the bottom -Deep water -Points -Drop offs Deep docks Bluff walls'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on September 02, 2021. May be an image of ‎text that says '‎SET-UP your favorite finesse set which usually means light line and a spinning rod! آم MAKE SURE YOU SAVE IT‎'‎.

node.text: How many of these hybrids have you caught?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on August 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'POPULAR HYBRIDS'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on August 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'WIPER Common names: Wiper, Hybrid Striped Bass, Whiterock Bass, Sunshine Bass, Palmetto Bass, Rocket Bass Parent species: Striped Bass and White Bass Defining features: Their lateral lines will be broken up, rather than the clean lines of a striper.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on August 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TIGER MUSKIE Common names: Tiger Muskie Parent species: Muskie and Northern Pike Defining features: Has a broken vertical bar pattern and ạ palish green/yellow color. Muskie cạn have similar patterns, but are not as distinct as the tiger muskie pattern.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on August 31, 2021. May be an image of body of water and text that says 'MEAN MOUTH Common names: Mean Mouth, Hybrid Smallmouth Bass Parent species: Smallmouth Bass and Spotted Bass, OR Smallmouth Bass and Largemouth Bass Defining features: A brownish/greenish color, with the mixed patterns of the two fish. mouth is bigger than a typical smallmouth's.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on August 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'SAUGEYE Common names: Saugey Parent species: Sauger and Walleye Defining features: Has a gold body with distinct brown blotches, and a subtle white pigment at end of tail. Dorsal fin has spots and bars in webbing, whereas saugers only have spots.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on August 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TIGER TROUT Common names: Tiger Trout Parent species: Brown Trout and Brook Trout Defining features: Has a dark and distinct maze-like pattern on its brownish/gray body. The belly is a bright yellow/orange.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on August 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'SPLAKE Common names: Splake, Slake, Frankenfish Parent species: Male Brook Trout and Female Lake Trout Defining features: Splake have similar coloration as brook trout, but a forked tail like lake trout, They also grow faster and live longer than brook trout.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on August 31, 2021. May be an image of body of water and text that says 'CUTBOW TROUT Common names: Cutbow Parent species Cutthroat Trout and Rainbow Trout Defining features: They can have a wide range of characteristics. Usually, they'll have a red/orange patch near the jaw, and a pink/red lateral line on the body.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on August 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'SUNFISH HYBRID Parent species: There are more than 20 combinations of hybrid sunfish that have been discovered. Above is a bluegill and green sunfish hybrid. Defining features: To get better at identifying hybrid sunfish, learn the main features of popular sunfish like bluegill, green sunfish, redear, longear, pumpkinseed and the list goes on and on.'.

Photo by Karl’s Bait & Tackle on August 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says '"Every single thing in this entire universe either is or is not a sukoshi bug." -Karl VonDibble 10000FISH'.
